<div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent"><br />I'm not sure "most games did it the other way". Earlier games seemed to favor vertical mirroring, but later in the console's life, several high profile games, including SMB3, Kirby and Mega Man games, decided to use horizontal mirroring and deal with attribute glitches at the sides of the screen. I find that horrible, I'd never accept that in a game of mine.<br /></div><br />Do you find glitches horrible in <a href="http://jonathan.microclub.ch/dummy/multiscroll.nes" class="postlink">this demo</a> as well ? I bet someone who don't know they exist and that plays on a real TV will not ever notice them.<br />I'm going to try to make it a multi-directional scroller, but as I said above it becomes a headache as soon as you mix both directions, even if you don't have to decode metatiles or compressed maps.<br /><br />PS : If someone have a request of a map to test my engine, please go away (but it should be easy to scroll trough the map freely so I can take savestates).<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=38">Bregalad</a> — Sat Mar 20, 2010 1:55 pm</p><hr />
